                    communication.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Initial Hand Position:</strong> Start with your hand open, all fingers extended, and
                        palm facing forward.</li>
                    <li><strong>Index Finger Extension:</strong> Keep your index finger extended straight up, pointing
                        upwards.</li>
                    <li><strong>Thumb Positioning:</strong> Extend your thumb outward, forming a right angle with the
                        index finger.</li>
                    <li><strong>Curling Other Fingers:</strong> Curl your middle, ring, and pinky fingers into your
                        palm. They should be held firmly against the palm, emphasizing the 'L' shape created by the
                        thumb and index finger.</li>
                    <li><strong>Ensure Clarity:</strong> Maintain the right angle between the index finger and thumb
                        clearly. The hand should be steady, and the sign held at eye level for visibility.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Practice forming the 'L' sign to ensure it's easily recognizable. This letter is frequently used in
